<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-09-07T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-09-07T20:00:00-05:00" n="359" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d359">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/3781: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Welles</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-09-07T20:00:00-05:00">September 7, 1933—8
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 8:42 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>210. A meeting is called for 10 o’clock tonight at the Palace which
                                will be attended by the leaders of all political groups. I am
                                reliably informed that the revolutionary group in control will then
                                turn over the Government and I am further advised that President
                                Céspedes will be restored as head of the Government.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>